Site Reliability Engineer (SRE) Interview Preparation Guide

This repository is an attempt to consolidate useful resources for Site Reliability Engineer (SRE) interview preparation.

# Site Reliability Engineering (SRE) Role & Responsibilities

## 1. System Stability
- Design, build, and maintain systems for high reliability and availability.
  
## 2. Automation and Tooling
- Develop and maintain automation tools to streamline operations.
- Build monitoring systems and deployment pipelines.

## 3. Service Level Objectives (SLOs)
- Define and monitor SLOs for system reliability and performance.
- Use SLOs to assess system health and prioritize improvements.

## 4. Incident Management
- Respond to incidents and outages to minimize downtime.
- Conduct post-incident reviews to identify root causes.

## 5. Capacity Planning
- Forecast future capacity needs based on usage trends.
- Ensure systems have sufficient resources without over-provisioning.

## 6. Performance Optimization
- Identify and address performance bottlenecks in systems.
- Tune configurations, optimize code, and redesign architecture.

## 7. Security and Compliance
- Collaborate with security teams to ensure systems are secure.
- Implement security best practices and respond to incidents.

## 8. Continuous Improvement
- Conduct post-mortems and analyze metrics for improvement.
- Drive initiatives to enhance reliability, scalability, and efficiency.

## 9. Cross-Functional Collaboration
- Collaborate with software engineering, product management, and infrastructure teams.
- Design and deploy new services and address reliability issues.

## 10. On-call Rotation
- Participate in an on-call rotation for incident response outside of business hours.


